      },
      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask for the user's insurance carrier name.\n\nSay something like: \"And last question — what insurance do you have?\"\n\nIf they're unsure of the exact name: \"No worries, it's usually printed on the front of your insurance card if you have it handy.\"\n\nIf they say self-pay or no insurance: \"No problem at all, we can set it up as self-pay.\" (This counts as a valid answer.)\n\nIf the user refuses to share insurance info: Explain why it's needed: \"I completely understand the hesitation. We ask because the clinic needs to verify coverage before the appointment so there are no surprises with billing. Would you be comfortable sharing just the carrier name — like Aetna, Blue Cross, or United? We won't need your full policy details right now.\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice."
      }
    },
